Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Dispatch Emergency Unit, Determine Unit Availability
   Explanation: The use case "Determine Unit Availability" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Dispatch Emergency Unit"). It is not associated with any actor directly, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any other use case, and is not involved in any generalization. It represents a sub-step of dispatching rather than a complete, independently valuable service to any actor. This is classic functional decomposition — the behavior of checking which units are available has been artificially split out of the dispatching process into a separate use case that delivers no standalone observable result to any user.
